            <pb n="1"/>
            <opener> Transkript. <lb/> Bil.10 <note>Handwritten comments in upper left
                    corner.</note>
                <dateline rend="text-align: right">
                    <date when="1931-09-09">September 9, 1931.</date>
                </dateline>
                <persName rend="text-align: left"><roleName type="honorific">Miss</roleName>
                    <forename>Ida</forename>
                    <surname>von Schulzenheim</surname></persName>,<lb/>
                <address>
                    <street>Riddaregatan 78,</street>
                    <lb/>
                    <name>Stockholm,</name>
                    <country>Sweden.</country>
                    <lb/>
                </address>
            </opener>

            <p> Dear <roleName type="honorific">Miss</roleName>
                <surname>von Schulzenheim</surname>:<lb/>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Dividing row of colons and hyphens</figDesc>
                </figure> <lb/></p> <p rend="indent"> As yet I have been unable to do anything in the <surname>Bendix</surname>
                matter.<lb/> His private affairs have not been settled and until these have
                been<lb/> cleared up it seems impossible to do anything with him.
                        <name><foreign>“Soldyrkaren”</foreign></name><lb/> and <name>“Crocus”</name>
                have both been returned to <placeName>the Building</placeName>.<lb/>
            </p>
            <figure>
                <figDesc>Dividing row of colons and hyphens</figDesc>
            </figure> <lb/>
            <closer rend="indent"> Regretting the delay in replying to your letters, and with<lb/> best wishes and
                greetings, I am<lb/>
                <salute rend="text-align: right">Sincerely yours,</salute><lb/>
                <signed rend="text-align: right"><forename>Amandus</forename>
                    <surname>Johnson</surname>.</signed><lb/>
            </closer>
        </body>
